[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="ZoneDef" load_steps=12 format=3]

; W2-T3 retrofit (`86c9y1045`, SI-8 (b) lock) — single S1 ZoneDef covering
; the full Stratum-1 narrative arc. All 8 hand-authored S1 chunks are
; declared as anchors per the SI-8 (b) commitment ("partially procedural
; with hand-pinned set-pieces"); the procedural slot pool is intentionally
; SMALL (3 rooms × max 1 slot per gap) so per-character variance reads
; without diluting the deliberate narrative ordering.
;
; Anchors (in zone-graph order — narrative-ordered):
;   1. entry         → s1_room01 (Threshold — practice dummy; player intro)
;   2. npc_room      → s1_room02 (Antechamber — quiet, room for a stationary NPC)
;   3. story_beat    → s1_room03 (Charger's Run — first chase-archetype intro)
;   4. quest_target  → s1_room04 (Marksman's Perch — Shooter-only chunk;
;                                 "find the marksman" objective room)
;   5. story_beat    → s1_room05 (Crossfire Yard — mixed-archetype trial)
;   6. npc_room      → s1_room06 (Hallowed Spring — healing fountain in
;                                 MultiMobRoom; restful NPC slot)
;   7. story_beat    → s1_room07 (Pincer Hall — multi-shooter pressure beat)
;   8. boss_room     → s1_room08 (Bossward Threshold — boss_door port
;                                 toward Stratum1BossRoom.tscn)
;   9. exit          → s1_z1_descent (re-uses s1_room08 chunk GEOMETRY but
;                                     distinct anchor room_id; demonstrates
;                                     "two anchors may share chunk geometry,
;                                     must have distinct room_ids" per
;                                     ZoneAnchor.gd doc).
;                      target_zone_id = &"s2_z1_entry_hall" — cross-zone
;                      mating per level-chunks.md § "Cross-zone transitions".
;                      Re-targeted in W3-T7 Stage 4 (ticket 86c9y7ygj Part C)
;                      after Sponsor locked S2 names 2026-05-24 — the Stage 1
;                      shells (PR #360) authored `s2_z1_entry_hall` per the
;                      lock; this anchor was still pointing at the pre-lock
;                      `s2_z1_sunken_entrance` slug. One-line fix per the
;                      Stage 4 dispatch brief's exit-anchor-mismatch hook.
;
; Procedural slot pool: 3 mid-tier combat chunks (rooms 03 / 05 / 07). All
; three carry the canonical WEST entry + EAST exit ports + non-trivial mob
; spawns, so per-character procedural fill remains combat-shaped without
; producing dead corridors.
;
; Slot range: [0, 1] per gap × 8 gaps = 0..8 procedural chunks per assembly.
; Total chunks per assembly: 9 (anchor-only floor) .. 17 (max fill). The
; SMALL fill range (vs the spike's [1, 3]) is the SI-8 (b) "light
; procedural fill between anchors" commitment — narrative reads first,
; per-character variance second.
;
; W2-T3 acceptance: assemble across N≥8 seeds → port_mating_errors stays
; empty (s1_room01 east-seam fix in same PR closes R-PROCGEN.b). Pinned by
; tests/test_floor_assembler.gd::test_s1_z1_clean_mating_across_8_seeds.

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/level/ZoneDef.gd" id="1_zone"]
[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/level/ZoneAnchor.gd" id="2_anchor"]

